<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-73-0791 </DOCNO><TEXT>As an initial parameter approach to meet the industrial need for a wastagemodel describing the possible consequences of leakage from a fast breederreactor system generator, the Perceval and Envolvee codes correctly predictthe tube penetration time and material erosion volume during an incident.The correlation of the formulas presented here will soon be improvedby introducing additional dimensionless numbers such as a modified Froudenumber. Ungoing experiments in the Jonas and Super-Jonas test facilitieswill provide further experimental data to develop these formulas. Thedirection of sodium flow in the heat exchanger tube bundle has a significantrole in wastage, and will therefore also be included in the formulations.</TEXT></DOC>